radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated, up to 1.0 cm, with wall hyperenhancement. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. The liver shows a small subcentimeter hypodensity in the right peripheral hepatic lobe. No evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation. The pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, and rectum are all within normal limits. No free fluid in the pelvis. No lymphadenopathy. No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
